(97, 1, '2012-12-04 06:06:58', '2012-12-04 06:06:58', '[applet code="P1.class" file="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/fermat-point-calculation.jar" width="500" height="500"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo calculate the shortest path between the three points, click and drag the vertices of the triangle (A, B, and C).\r\n\r\nSource code: <a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/code/fermat/fermat.pde">P1</a>\r\nCreated by <i>Russell Strauss</i>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nCS3451 - Fall 2010 taught by Jarek Rossignac\r\n\r\nProblem:\r\nThree points can be placed anywhere in space. Find the path of least distance that connects all three points. The program must be dynamic and controlled by the user.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nIn a triangle, the point that connects all three vertices with the least amount of distance is known as the Fermat Point {citation <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermat_point">here</a>}.\r\nCalculating the Fermat Point consists of the following steps:\r\n1. Determine whether the triangle has any angle greater than (or equal to) 120 degrees. If so, then the Fermat Point is the vertex of the angle that is greater than 120 degrees.\r\n2. If no angles are greater than 120 degrees, then form three equilateral triangles created by each edge of the original triangle created by A, B, and C.\r\n3. Form lines connecting the outer vertex of each equilateral triangle to the opposite vertex of the original triangle (A, B, or C).\r\n4. Where these lines intersect is the Fermat Point. The paths connecting the three points with the least amount of distance are the paths from each vertex to the Fermat Point, represented above by the lightest shade of blue.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Solution in pseudocode:</b>\r\n<i>\r\n</i>[crayon url="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/code/fermat/fermat.txt" /]\r\n\r\nNote: This is only the highly simplified pseudocode. To see the exact code with in-depth comments, see the source code <a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/code/fermat/fermat.pde">here</a>.\r\nZip file <a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/code/fermat/fermat.zip">here</a>.', 'Fermat Point Calculation', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'geometric-shortest-distance-between-three-points', '', '', '2012-12-19 06:39:07', '2012-12-19 06:39:07', '', 0, 'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=97', 25, 'portfolio-piece', '', 0),
