(117, 1, '2012-12-06 02:46:31', '2012-12-06 02:46:31', 'Problem statement:\n<div>\n\n<em>A connection between postmodernism and poststructuralism is a shift from a single, authoritarian voice to multiple perspectives. In postmodernism, this shift manifests itself in a hybrid aesthetic. Poststructuralism emphasizes the importance of identity in interpretation; it posits a person''s gender, race, sexuality, class, ethnicity, and age affect viewpoint.</em>\n\n<em>For this second assignment, develop a multi-page project that modifies a traditional myth, legend, fable or fairy tale through the filters of postmodernism and poststructuralism. For example, you could change the gender, race or sexuality of a myth''s main character. You could make marginal characters the main characters. You could alter the location and era of the text. You could mix the narrative structure with new narratives or create a narrative that presents multiple perspectives. Look for ways to alter your myth/legend/fable/fairy tale, connecting it to your life and interests.</em>\n\n<em>Expand upon the design elements and principles you incorporated in your poster. Emphasize the visual aspects of your narrative; look for inspiration in graphic novels and film storyboards. Issues of image-making, framing and composition come to the fore. And since this is a multi-page project, consciously consider issues of sequencing and timing.</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe myth I chose to modify is the fable of the city mouse and the country mouse. While the city mouse is always busy, the country mouse has a very slow and modest life. Unlike this myth, mine comes to a slightly different conclusion.\n\n</div>\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a style="text-align: center; width: 100%; font: 32px ''Raleway''; font-weight: 200; text-shadow: 5px 5px 8px black;" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg1.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">view narrative</a></p>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg2.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg2.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg3.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg3.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg4.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg4.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg5.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg5.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg6.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg6.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg7.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg7.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg8.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg8.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg9.jpg" rel="shadowbox[david]">\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg9.jpg" alt="David" />\n</a>\n<a class="cente