(465, 1, '2012-12-14 07:14:27', '2012-12-14 07:14:27', 'Red Carpet Rush is an Atari game I made with two other students. We programmed in from scratch in Batari Basic, a slight modification of BASIC, specialized for programming for the Atari 2600.\r\n\r\nClick <a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Red-Carpet-Rush.zip">here</a> to download the game and play it. The game file is "RedCarpetRush.bas.bin." If you double click on it, your system will probably read it as an archived file, so either open Stella first and then open the game file or drag the game file to the Stella icon. Stella is the Atari emulator that allows Atari games to run on a computer.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="view-manual" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Red-Carpet-Rush-User-Manual-1.jpg" rel="shadowbox[manual]">View game manual</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-1.png"><img class="center size-full wp-image-483" alt="rcr-screenshot-1" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-1.png" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-2.png"><img style="width: 100%;" class="center size-full wp-image-484" alt="rcr-screenshot-2" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-2.png" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-3.png"><img style="width: 100%;" class="center size-full wp-image-485" alt="rcr-screenshot-3" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/rcr-screenshot-3.png" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a class="center" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Red-Carpet-Rush-User-Manual-2.jpg" rel="shadowbox[manual]">\r\n<img style="display: none; height: 1px;" alt="David" src="http://portf