(466, 1, '2012-12-14 07:15:38', '2012-12-14 07:15:38', 'Pikachu''s Revenge is a simple game in which the player takes it upon himself to redeem Pikachu''s reputation. Pikachu is tired of being called a "cute, little mouse," and is ready to show the world what he''s got. The player takes control of Pikachu in a fighting-style game in order to take his revenge upon the world. This game was an extension of one of our smaller homework assignments, Pikachu Frenzy. If I had more time to work on this, I would have loved to make the gameplay better, adding in more advanced fighting moves that would make the piece feel more like a game and less of a demonstration of my Game Boy programming. The game was programmed completely from scratch, bottom up. It will run perfectly if loaded onto a physical Game Boy Advance. To play the game, download the zip file <a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/GBA-games-by-Russell-Strauss.zip">here</a>. Then, open the .gba file with one of the Game Boy Advance emulators included in the zip file. Both Macintosh and Windows versions are included. If you cannot get the .gba file to open, try dragging it onto the emulator''s icon. You may also have to configure the emulator''s input configuration, which you can do in the Visual Boy Advance menu. The controls are: left and right to move, A to run, and B, L, R, up, and down to perform different attacks.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table style="width: 100%;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;"><a title="Title Screen" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/pr-title.bmp" rel="shadowbox[pika]">\r\n<img class="center" style="margin: 15px auto;" title="Title Screen" alt="screenshot" src="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/pr-title.bmp" />\r\n</a></td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;"><a title="Win Screen" href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/pr-win.bmp" rel="shadowbox[pika]">\r\n<i