(593, 1, '2013-05-30 16:28:33', '2013-05-30 16:28:33', '<img style="margin: 0 0 20px 20px;" title="me" alt="me" src="/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/me.jpeg" align="right" />\r\n\r\nI was born in Atlanta in 1989 and have lived in the metro Atlanta area my entire life. I am a graduate of the Georgia Institute of Technology with my undergraduate degree in Computational Media. I love working on projects that push my creativity to new levels and collaborating with people to create amazing products. I have a passion for creating things and one of my favorite things in life is to sit back and look upon something I have created as I observe and let it soak in. Though I look at the big picture and don’t let smalls things get me caught up, I sometimes have slight perfectionist tendencies with a high attention to detail and will not rest until something is absolutely polished and satisfactory.\r\n\r\nIn my free time, I always love to be doing something different. Life is full of endless opportunities, so I don’t like to waste it sitting around or being bored. Though I enjoy consistency, I am adventurous. I love to knit, ride my bike, hang out with my dog, build things, and participate in any activity that I think will make me a better or more diverse, open-minded, creative, or unique person. I love to create something out of nothing, and I love creating anything with my hands--anything from carpentry to cooking to web applications to knitting. Whenever I''m not doing something like this, I love to spend time with my friends and family.\r\n\r\nI have a deep feeling of responsibility to show kindness to others in everything that I do. I can relate to others easily and therefore always do my best to treat others as I would like to be treated myself. I love being around people and can work very well with others. I am always completely honest and supportive of others.\r\n\r\n<img style="margin: 0 20px 5px 0;" title="me and melissa" alt="me and melissa" src="/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/me-and-melissa.jpeg" align="left" />\r\n\r\nI am very self-motivated. I don''t do things because I have to, but because I want to see the results. Because of this, I can work well by myself and don''t have any trouble solving problems on my own. I am intelligent and can quickly adapt to situations and learn new things, especially when those are areas that interest me. I one day want to be extremely skilled at what I do—until then, I can only focus and try to improve each day.\r\n\r\nI am a very balanced person. I have not yet found what I want to do for my entire life, but am good at many things. Though I have not found any one thing specifically that I am most talented at, I can do a good job at almost anything I try.\r\n\r\nI am very people oriented and prefer to work with others. When I am concentrating or performing tedious tasks, I work best on my own, but my creativity flows best around other people, and I thoroughly enjoy working on creative (or team) projects with others.\r\n\r\nI have become very efficient at managing my time over the years due to my rigorous school workload, and I can judge my own abilities, knowing either when a project is out of my own range of potential or not. I love to always do something different, which is exactly why I have chosen to work with digital media over the years.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-05-30 16:28:33', '2013-05-30 16:28:33', '', 10, 'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/10-revision-15/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
