(608, 1, '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '<div class="section">\r\n<h1>Contact</h1>\r\n<div class="left">+ Home Address\r\n+ Phone\r\n+ E-mail\r\n+ Portfolio</div>\r\n<div class="right">44 Aberdeen Street Atlanta, GA 30307\r\n678.927.3289\r\nrussell@soldesignco.com\r\n<a href="http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net">http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net</a></div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="section">\r\n<h1>Education</h1>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">+ Undergraduate</div>\r\n<div class="right">Georgia Institute of Technology\r\nBS Computational Media ''12\r\nCum Laude\r\nGPA 3.5</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div><br/>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">+ High School</div>\r\n<div class="right">Dacula High School\r\nDacula, GA\r\nCum Laude\r\nGPA 3.6</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="section">\r\n<h1>Skills</h1>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">+ Coding Experience</div>\r\n<div class="right">- PHP, jQuery, Javascript, SQL, Unix, WordPress, Drupal, Python, Java, C, Basic, SmallTalk, XML\r\n- Can quickly adapt to new languages and syntax without much difficulty\r\n- Knowledge of styling standards, clear and concise commenting habits\r\n- Valid markup habits</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<br/>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">+ Design</div>\r\n<div class="right">- HMTL5, CSS3, XHTML, cross-browser compatibility\r\n- Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere, Flash\r\n- Final Cut Pro\r\n- Autodesk Maya</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection"><br/>+ Can communicate clearly and effectively, work under strict deadlines, balance multiple projects at once\r\n+ Can easily work well independently or with others, highly self-motivated\r\n+ Extremely high attention to detail&nbsp;\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="section">\r\n<h1>Awards</h1>\r\n<div class="subsection">+ One of Computational Media''s "Most Outstanding Students" in the degree\r\n+ Dean''s List each semester Fall 2008 to Spring 2012\r\n+ Best school-wide Foreign Language Student in high school</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="section work-experience">\r\n<h1>Work Experience</h1>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">May 2012 - present</div>\r\n<div class="right">SolDesign Company\r\n<em>Front &amp; Back-end Web Developer</em>\r\nSolDesign is a small 12-person Web Agency that specializes in both Web Design and Web Development. We design, build, host, and maintain sites for our clients, doing all work in-house. My roles as a developer at SolDesign vary: front-end & back-end development, server management, site architecture, client management, migration, content management, and debugging & updating outdated products.</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">December 2011 - May 2012</div>\r\n<div class="right">Crawford Media Services\r\n<em>Front &amp; Back-end Web Developer</em>\r\nI was hired as a contractor for six months to build a new web site for Crawford that would improve upon their current design and showcase their skill in the video production industry. I worked on the front-end and back-end of the site, communicating with the design team and interpreting the functional requirements for Crawford while critiquing the quality of the design and user experience of the site''s interface.</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">May 2011 - August 2012</div>\r\n<div class="right">The Children''s School\r\n<em>Robotics Teacher</em>\r\nThe Children''s School is a private school in Atlanta next to Piedmont Park. I taught the sixth grade technology class Computer Science and Robotics weekly using Lego NXT Mindstorms and basic lessons in the fundamentals of computing and procedural programming.</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">August 2009 - May 2012</div>\r\n<div class="right">Institute for Computing Education\r\n<em>Summer Camp Director, Workshop Leader, Inventory Manager</em>\r\nThe Institute for Computing Education is a research institute funded by the National Science Foundation dedicated to raising interest in Computer Science among kids elementary through high school, especially among women and minorities. I led eight weeks of summer camps each summer, taught workshops throughout the school year, and managed their inventory throughout the year.</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">January 2009 - August 2010</div>\r\n<div class="right">Office of Success Programs\r\n<em>Undergraduate Tutor</em>\r\nTutoring other undergrads in Computer Science and Spanish.</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="section references">\r\n<h1>References</h1>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">Tamara Weinstein</div>\r\n<div class="right">The Children''s School, Technology Specialist\r\ntamaraw@thechildrensschool.com\r\n404.835.4602</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">Barb Ericson</div>\r\n<div class="right">Institute for Computing Education, Director\r\nbe15@mail.gatech.edu\r\n404.702.7993</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="subsection">\r\n<div class="left">Michael Allenberg</div>\r\n<div class="right">Crawford Media Services\r\nUser Interface Designer\r\nmallenberg@crawford.com\r\n678.641.2914</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Resume', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '', 77, 'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/77-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
